title: U.S. identifies Navy SEALs who died attempting to seize Iranian arms
description: Two Navy SEALs, Christopher Chambers and Nathan Gage Ingram, died in a mishap while attempting to intercept a boat smuggling Iranian weapons, officials said.

title: Pressure mounts on Israel over its rejection of two-state solution
description: Israel instead is escalating its assault on Khan Younis in the southern Gaza Strip, sparking a new wave of people fleeing what were once designated safe zones.

title: Over 1 million rally in Germany against rising power of far-right party
description: After months of surging popularity of the AfD, a report disclosing that the party discussed expelling foreigners appears to have served as a wake-up call for many Germans.

title: In photos: The inauguration on Modi’s controversial Hindu temple
description: On Monday, as Prime Minister Narendra Modi inaugurated a grand Hindu temple on the site of the razed mosque, he spoke not of contrition but of justice won and pride restored — of a glorious new epoch awaiting the believers of Lord Ram like him.

title: Why do dogs wag their tails? Humans liked the rhythm, study suggests.
description: The findings flip the long-held belief that dogs wag their tails when happy, and instead suggest tail wags made people happy, so we selected for the trait.

title: Israel-Gaza war live updates: Netanyahu rejects Hamas’s terms for release of hostages; Gaza death toll passes 25,000
description: The Israeli prime minister dismissed what he said were Hamas’s conditions for the release of hostages, including the end of the war and the withdrawal of Israeli forces.

title: They were ready to give up on Israel. Now they’re all in.
description: The Hamas attack of Oct. 7 has spurred many liberal Israelis to reassess their relationship with the state.

title: Modi’s consecration of controversial Hindu temple caps years-long campaign
description: The destruction of a mosque on the site in Ayodhya, India, triggered deadly religious riots.

title: What Netanyahu sees from the river to the sea
description: The original party platform of Benjamin Netanyahu’s ruling Likud party insists that “between the Sea and the Jordan there will be only Israeli sovereignty.”
